I actually wish that CSS didn&#x27;t have so many different ways to write a rule. Have just one way to write a rule and enforce it strictly.<p>In other words, instead of being able to write any of these<p><pre><code>  padding: 0 0 0 0;
</code></pre>
OR<p><pre><code>  padding-top: 0;
</code></pre>
OR<p><pre><code>  padding: 0;
</code></pre>
Just settle on one (the first one in my opinion for this rule) and get rid of all the other alternatives.

